## Implementation order

1. ALTER `suppliers` — add `booking_system text`
2. `experience_option`
3. `availability_slot`
4. `booking` + `booking_line`
5. `external_ref`
6. `webhook_event`
7. `sync_cursor`

## Data flow

```
Provider API / Webhook → webhook_event (immutable, payload stored)
                       → projection columns updated on webhook_event
                       → canonical tables (booking, booking_line, etc.)
```

## Status normalization

Normalize provider statuses to canonical values:
`draft`, `on_hold`, `reserved`, `pending`, `confirmed`, `rejected`, `cancelled`, `expired`, `failed`, `redeemed`, `no_show`, `rebooked`, `unknown`

Per-provider mapping tables are in `msg-data_model/platform_mappings.md`.

## External references

All provider IDs MUST be stored in `external_ref`. This enables bidirectional lookup without scanning business tables.
